{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"skyborne-rebuffable-butterfly","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. On origin/main with `[identity] require_authenticated = true` (Gerrit change 759 / commit 8bb261c19), push any commit.\n2. The `verify-identity` merge-gate (`.github/workflows/verify-identity.yaml`, post-merge on the GitHub mirror) runs `rebar verify-identity` over the whole store.\n3. Observe: `verify-identity: FAIL — 182 enforced in-scope event(s) are not verified` — every push to main goes red.\n\n**Expected:** with write-signing rolled out, the whole store verifies clean under enforcement.\n**Actual:** 182 enforced events fail: 2 unsigned `COMPLETION_VERDICT` sidecars + 180 `key_not_valid_at_era`.\n\n## Root cause (both experimentally confirmed)\n\n- **Source 1 — reducer-ignored sidecars are wrongly in the gate's scope.** `COMPLETION_VERDICT` (and siblings `REVIEW_RESULT`/`TICKET_DIGEST`/`ENQUEUE_ENRICH`) are NOT in `reducer.KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES` (non-state-bearing observability), yet `verify_authorship._event_from_file` classifies them. Emitted best-effort-unsigned when no signing key resolves, they become enforced failures. This is a mechanism-2 artifact (completion verification) whose store event fell into mechanism-1 (identity write-signing) scope.\n- **Source 2 — compaction persists `commit_sha: null`.** `compact._build_authorship_ledger` records `null` when `resolve_event_commit` returns None at fold time and retires the raw file; the gate can't re-resolve the null, fail-closes it to ENFORCED, and mis-classifies validly-signed, era-valid events as `key_not_valid_at_era` (`verify_authorship.py` :206-220,:249-270).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `verify_authorship._event_from_file` skips events whose `event_type` is not in `reducer.KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES` (reducer-ignored sidecars), proven by a test where a `COMPLETION_VERDICT` on a work ticket is NOT an enforced failure while a KNOWN unsigned `STATUS`/`CREATE` still IS. (`src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py`)\n- [ ] The gate re-resolves a LEDGER entry whose recorded `commit_sha` is null via `authorship.resolve_position_commit(position, tracker)` before the era/enforcement decision, proven by a test that a null-commit, era-valid signed ledger entry classifies `verified` not `key_not_valid_at_era`. (`src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py`)\n- [ ] `compact._build_authorship_ledger` never persists `commit_sha: null` when the position is resolvable — it falls back to `resolve_position_commit`; proven by a monkeypatched unit test. (`src/rebar/_commands/compact.py`)\n- [ ] Regression tests added under `tests/unit/` and the full suite passes; `make lint` clean.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] `verify-identity` is added as a pre-merge job in the Gerrit `Verified` gate (`.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml`) so the whole-store enforcement check runs BEFORE merge, not only post-merge (mitigates the prior epics' gap).\n- [ ] [operator-attested] After the fixes land, `rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated` over the whole store reports 0 enforced-not-verified, and `require_authenticated` is re-enabled on main with a freshly pinned `enforce_since`.\n\n## Context\n\nRemediation of the incomplete identity-signing rollout (epics e68d built, dc09 rolled out). Prior epics verified via a producer-side window scan + force-closes and never ran the whole-store-under-enforcement check; this bug fixes the two escaped defect classes and hardens the process. Rollback of the premature flip landed as Gerrit change 767.","id":"3f42-81a9-6f87-4e13","parent_id":"","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"verify-identity false-rejects reducer-ignored sidecars + null-commit ledger entries — blocks safe require_authenticated enforcement"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784322891869304001,"uuid":"a4fdbef2-3663-4dd7-920f-66677f34aba6"}